HEADWORD: Sourde
<hw>Sourde</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sourdre</ets>. See <er>Source</er>.]</ety> <def>To have origin or
source; to rise; to spring.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now might men ask whereof that pride <qex>sourdeth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Souring</ent>⟦br⟧
